{"word":"H1351 - גָּאַל - gâʼal - gaw-al' - Defile","slug":"H1351","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">גָּאַל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>gâʼal"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>gaw-al'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Defile"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D2;&#x05BC;&#x05D0;&#x05DC; - ga&#x0302;'al</b> - <i>gaw-al'</i><p/>A primitive root, (rather identical with <a href=\"#/H1350\">H1350</a>, through the idea of <i>freeing</i>, that is, <i>repudiating</i>); to <i>soil</i> or (figuratively) <i>desecrate: - </i>defile, pollute, stain."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1352\">H1352</a>"}]}